title: GOT - The Long Night Dizisinin Çekim Tarihi Belli Oldu
body:
GOT – The Long Night Dizisinin Çekim Tarihi Belli Oldu

Geçtiğimiz Haziran ayında HBO’dan pilot bölüm için resmi onayı alan yeni Game of Thrones dizisinin çekim tarihi belli oldu.

“Pilot bölüm yeni sipariş edildiği için projenin ilk aşamalarındayız ve bu yüzden dizinin henüz yönetmeni, oyuncu kadrosu, çekim mekanı, hatta ismi bile yok.” Martin dizinin adıyla ilgili kişisel tercihinin “The Long Night” olduğunu da açıkladı.

Game of Thrones’ta yaşanan…

summary: [SPOILERS] The bar is incredibly high for Game Of Thrones
title: [SPOILERS] The bar is incredibly high for Game Of Thrones
body:
I’ve heard people say they won’t really be happy with the ending, whatever it is, unless it’s not predictable at all, and all that makes me think is Damn! the bar is extremely high for a lot of people when it comes to Game Of Thrones, yes I know GoT has probably given us more OMG moments than any other tv show or movie in history but as the story comes to an end it also gets harder to give as many surprises when the characters are all developed and you can’t just change how they’ve acted the whole series (which would indeed be bad writing if they did that). I honestly thought “Breaking Bad is in my top 3 fav shows ever (Along with GoT) but damn I’m sure all of us saw the ending coming (Walt dying while saving Jesse and finally admitting to his wife that he did all those things because he actually enjoyed it) a mile away” it was a predictable ending and a great one, I feel Game Of Thrones has become so big and has masterfully created a fantasy world where almost everything seems to click, that now we nitpick the show on every minor detail (expectations for S8 are just one example).

I guess it goes to show how it’s made us grow to expect the very best from it. :)



Source: https://ift.tt/2wMjH5P

title: 5th September 2018
body:
I have absurdly vivid dreams.

Erin Morgenstern

I woke up early again this morning, but felt unusually perky after the usual round of epic dreams.

I have been consistently waking up at six a.m. for weeks now, exhausted and panting, having escaped the White Walkers for the umpteenth time.  Oh Freud, what would you say about me?

But, I’ve moved on from binge watching Game of Thrones, along with…

summary: Over the past few days there were unofficial rumors that season 8 might be delayed until 2020, I don’t want to go too much into...
caption:
Over the past few days there were unofficial rumors that season 8 might be delayed until 2020, I don’t want to go too much into it since it’s fake news
(but basically a special effects artist for the show said their work on season 8 might not be eligible for the 2019 Emmys, and it’ll be eligible for the 2020 Emmys, as the cutoff date is May 31, 2019 (leading everyone to assume the show will be delayed).
-
However, HBO clarified that that’s not true, and that ALL episodes of the final season will air during the first half of 2019, before the 2019 Emmy eligibility cut off date.
-
MEANING - ALL EPISODES OF SEASON 8 WILL AIR BEFORE MAY 31, 2019!!!!
-
This is huge!! This means that the show will most probably air in April!❄️ So bittersweet!
-
(Just in case you were wondering why I didn’t post the delay rumor when it came out, it’s because I rarely post rumors, I doubted it would be delayed, & I felt it wasn’t true or reliable; I listened to my gut and I was right! Plus, ICYMI, we kinda already knew it would be April/May since a few weeks ago an actor from told us so at LFCC! Look through my posts or my LFCC highlight to see haha)

summary: HBO released a trailer of its 2019 lineup (footage from all the new seasons of their shows that are being released in 2019) and...
caption:
HBO released a trailer of its 2019 lineup (footage from all the new seasons of their shows that are being released in 2019) and most of the Game of Thrones footage shown was from season 7, but if you look really closely there is this clip from season 8!
❄️
I don’t consider this a spoiler at all since we know it’s going to happen but I know some of my followers would consider it a spoiler so:
MINI SPOILER WARNING IF YOU WANT TO GO INTO SEASON 8 NOT KNOWING ANYTHING
‼️
In the tiny clip we see Jon back at Winterfell and reuniting with Sansa, who doesn’t seem too pleased if you ask me👀
🔥
The final, eighth season of Game of Thrones is premiering during the first half of 2019
